PewDiePie is the most subscribed user on YouTube, with over 57 million
subscribers as of October 2017.

This **list of most-subscribed YouTube channels** contains the top 50 channels
with the most subscribers on the video platform [YouTube](/wiki/YouTube
"YouTube").[1] The ability to "subscribe" to a user's channel was added to
YouTube by late October 2005,[2] and the "most subscribed" list on YouTube
began as a chart by May 2006, at which time [Smosh](/wiki/Smosh "Smosh") was
number one with fewer than 3,000 subscribers.[3] Since December 22, 2013, the
most subscribed user has been [PewDiePie](/wiki/PewDiePie "PewDiePie") with 57
million subscribers.

[Gaming](/wiki/Video_game "Video game"), [Sports](/wiki/Sport "Sport") and
[Movies](/wiki/Movie "Movie")) are not included. As of October 31, 2017, 29
out of the 50 top channels originate from [English-speaking
countries](/wiki/English_language "English language") (20 from the [United
States](/wiki/United_States "United States")) and 34 are English-language
channels.[1]

## Reactions[[edit](/w/index.php?title=List_of_most-
subscribed_YouTube_channels&action=edit&section=6 "Edit section: Reactions")]

In late 2006, when [Peter Oakley](/wiki/Peter_Oakley "Peter Oakley"), also
known as Geriatric1927, became most subscribed, a number of TV channels wanted
to interview him on his rise to fame. _[The Daily Mail](/wiki/Daily_Mail
"Daily Mail")_ and TechBlog did an article about him and his success. In 2009,
the [FRED](/wiki/Fred_Figglehorn "Fred Figglehorn") channel was the first to
have over one million subscribers.

Following the third time that [Smosh](/wiki/Smosh "Smosh") became most
subscribed, [Ray William Johnson](/wiki/Ray_William_Johnson "Ray William
Johnson") collaborated with the duo.[144] A flurry of top YouTubers including
[Ryan Higa](/wiki/Ryan_Higa "Ryan Higa"), [Shane Dawson](/wiki/Shane_Dawson
"Shane Dawson"), [Felix Kjellberg](/wiki/PewDiePie "PewDiePie"), [Michael
Buckley](/wiki/Michael_Buckley_\(Internet_celebrity\) "Michael Buckley
\(Internet celebrity\)"), [Kassem Gharaibeh](/wiki/KassemG "KassemG"), [The
Fine Brothers](/wiki/Fine_Brothers "Fine Brothers"), and Johnson himself,
congratulated the duo shortly after they surpassed Johnson as the most
subscribed channel.[145]
